{
  "slug": "teleport",
  "kind": "compose",
  "metadata": {
    "name": "Teleport",
    "description": "Runs Teleport in Docker Compose with local auth and proxy services plus a companion Teleport configuration file.",
    "guide": "## Overview\nRuns Teleport in Docker Compose with local auth and proxy services enabled.\n\n## Prerequisites\n- Reserve the public Teleport hostname and point it at the host running this stack.\n- Provide persistent storage for `/var/lib/teleport` so cluster identity survives container restarts.\n- If you front Teleport with Traefik, make sure the referenced network and TLS resolver already exist.\n\n## Deploy\n- Render `compose.yaml` and `config/teleport.yaml`, then start the stack with `docker compose up -d`.\n- Watch the container logs until the auth and proxy services are healthy.\n\n## Post-Install\n- Create the initial admin user with Teleport's user onboarding workflow after the cluster starts.\n- Complete MFA or WebAuthn enrollment and verify browser access through the public Teleport hostname.\n- Add nodes, apps, or Kubernetes integrations separately after the base cluster is working.\n\n## References\n- [Teleport Documentation](https://goteleport.com/docs/)\n- [Teleport Configuration Reference](https://goteleport.com/docs/reference/config/)",
    "tags": [],
    "template_version": "18.7.3",
    "icon": {
      "provider": "selfhst",
      "id": "teleport"
    },
    "draft": false
  },
  "variables": [
    {
      "title": "General",
      "variables": [
        {
          "name": "service_name",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Compose service name",
          "required": false,
          "default": "teleport",
          "description": "Name to use for the compose service.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "teleport"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "container_name",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Container name",
          "required": false,
          "default": "teleport",
          "description": "Name to use for the container.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "teleport"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "restart_policy",
          "type": "enum",
          "title": "Container restart policy",
          "required": true,
          "default": "unless-stopped",
          "description": "Policy used for Container Restart.",
          "config": {
            "options": [
              "unless-stopped",
              "always",
              "on-failure",
              "no"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "data_host_path",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Data Path",
          "required": false,
          "default": "./data",
          "description": "Host path for persistent Teleport data",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "./data"
          }
        }
      ],
      "name": "general"
    },
    {
      "title": "Configuration",
      "variables": [
        {
          "name": "teleport_node_name",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Teleport node name",
          "required": false,
          "default": "teleport-prod-1",
          "description": "Name to use for the teleport node.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "teleport-prod-1"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "teleport_public_host",
          "type": "str",
          "title": "Public Teleport hostname",
          "required": true,
          "description": "Hostname used for Public Teleport.",
          "config": {
            "placeholder": "tp.home.arpa"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "teleport_log_level",
          "type": "enum",
          "title": "Teleport log level",
          "required": false,
          "default": "INFO",
          "description": "Logging level used for Teleport Log.",
          "config": {
            "options": [
              "DEBUG",
              "INFO",
              "WARN",
              "ERROR"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "teleport_second_factor",
          "type": "enum",
          "title": "2FA Mode",
          "required": false,
          "default": "on",
          "description": "Teleport second factor mode",
